adviseScripts.text: The wind is awfully loud today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Don't you think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: It's almost as if... the wind is weeping.
I should have known.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I suppose ignorance is bliss for commoners.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Truly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: This wind may have carried something harmful into the Ark.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Let's hurry, before the wind stops.
It is agreed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I spend some meaningful time together with Guillotine.
*Ha. Ha*
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: *Tee hee hee*
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Ignore her.
Why are you laughing?
*Glance*
*Keep glancing*
Act like you didn't see anything.
Ha! A foolish question!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Today is the day the blood moon rises upon the abyss.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: That means the demon inside me will rise up as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: So this laughter is not mine. It is that of the Devil inside, which has been temporarily set free!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I beg of you, Partner. Do not come near me during this time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: If you get too close to me, I... could be dangerous to you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine leaves the room, her clothing flapping in an invisible breeze.
Partner, sometimes I...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I cannot bear the burden of blood lain upon me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: How... do you control this feeling?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Embrace it. It is what we must do.
Get some exercise. You'll feel better.
Is there really no other way?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I don't like it. Too much work.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I spend some meaningful time together with Guillotine.
I have to keep a low profile.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: The Big O has been extremely active the past few days.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: They may very well be eavesdropping on this very conversation.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: This place is safe. We're protected by the Aegis Barriers.
The Central Government has better things to do than spy on us.
What...!?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text:
... Ahem. Well, then.
This location is far more reliable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I wouldn't be so sure if I were you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: You'll end up with a knife in your back if you remain that complacent.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I spend some meaningful time together with Guillotine.
Recently, my SNS followers have been increasing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text:
They're all interested in the One-Winged Dark Lord sealed inside my right eye,
like moths to the flame.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text:
But if this continues,
The Big O is bound to notice my account.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I need your advice, Partner.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Should I block followers who have private accounts?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Just delete the account.
No. If you did that, none of our allies with hidden identities could contact you.
You can't be serious!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I wouldn't dream of doing that. Never.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: You have a point.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text:
I was not thinking straight.
Thank you for your help.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Guillotine about how to handle SNS followers.
Urgh...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: My right eye is tingling.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Could it be that the One-Winged Dark Lord's seal has been weakened?
Maybe it's just going to rain.
It could well be.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: It's as if I'm being infected by its madness...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: This is an Outpost. The weather isn't real. Even the rain is artificial.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Do you really think I'd have a pain in my eye just because of that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Guillotine about her health.
Partner, sometimes I wonder...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Can you even begin to comprehend my loneliness?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Yes, I do. I'm the only one who does.
What are you talking about?
Yes. This is my destiny.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: A Nikke assigned to dispose of other Nikkes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: What a terrible, lonely fate.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: It may not amount to much, but nevertheless, I'm glad that you understand my situation.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text:
I knew it.
No one can possibly understand what I'm going through.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: What a terrible hand I've been dealt in this life.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I spend some lonely time with Guillotine.
It feels like Maiden is keeping her distance from me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Why?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Could... she be afraid of the kotodama in my words?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: She's just shy.
She is not ready to accept your presence.
Tsk.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I thought she'd have gotten used to it by now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: If that's the case, I can understand.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: After all, I can be a bit of a handful sometimes. Hee hee.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I spend some meaningful time with Guillotine.
Exia.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Exia has been spying on my account recently.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I remember her being part of the Information Center at The Big O.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: What's she up to?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: She just thinks your posts are fun to read, that's all.
She's trying to sell you out to The Big O.
You really believe that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Hmph. You're slipping. You've let your guard down.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: You think so, too?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: In that case, I should block her at once.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I spend some meaningful time with Guillotine.
Partner...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: What would it be like to have a soulmate?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Someone who stays with you for the rest of your life?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: That would make me very happy.
The day I get married is the day I die.
Is that so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Well, whoever your soulmate is...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: is a very lucky person.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: *Cough cough*
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I wasn't asking about marriage!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I spend time with Guillotine talking about spouses.
I heard there's a thunderstorm brewing up on the surface.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Something doesn't feel right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: It's simply the energy emanating from the Dragon of the Deep.
There is a storm coming.
So you felt it as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Have you finally accepted the calling?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Do you think this is just a natural phenomenon?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: You have much to learn.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine and I speak more on the origin of the lightning storm.
Envy, jealousy, resentment...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I see it in the eyes of all who gaze upon me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: How can I find solace from their judgment?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: It's too late for us to escape.
Can we at least try to have a normal conversation?
I see, so this is yet another trial.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: We have always walked a different path from everyone else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: That is my destiny, and I will accept it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Communication...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I have tried so many times, but have never been able to breakthrough.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: In the end, none of us can overcome the hand that we have been dealt.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine and I have a conversation about fate.
Something isn't right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: My hands are shaking, and I feel so anxious...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: What is happening?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Someone is sending you a signal from another dimension.
You've got low blood sugar.
This body's abilities have seeped into other dimensions?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Argh, my power is escaping me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Anyway, got any chocolate Splendamin?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine and I have a nice heart-to-heart.
Music is a good friend when you are alone.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: What kind of music do you listen to when you're on your own?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Hymn of the Blood Moon.
Perfect Pitch
That's a pretty famous song, but I'm still surprised you know it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: It's perfect for when you're gazing at a blood moon in real life. Brings a tear to your eye...
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, we're not so different after all!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I thought I understood the preferences of normal people, but I guess not.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine and I had a conversation about music.
Sometimes I doubt whether I even truly exist.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Do I exist? Who am I?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Partner,
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: who do you think I am?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine de Mephisto.
My partner in crime.
Yes. I'm Guillotine de Mephisto.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: But what is a name but a mere jumbling together of letters?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: If I were to change my name, would I become someone different?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: You're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Forget the idea of Guillotine, forget everything.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: All I need to remember is that we are partners.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine and I have a deep philosophical discussion about existence.
I want to be alone.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Just let me be.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I won't let you suffer all alone!
Sigh... I knew you'd keep pestering me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Is this what they call comradery?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Hmmph.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Suddenly, I feel more lonely than before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I spend some lonely time with Guillotine.
If the world suddenly came to an end today,
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: how would you spend your last day?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I'd spend it with you.
I'd spend it by myself.
Thanks to you, this body will never be lonely.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: When that day comes, we will finally be liberated from our solitary existence.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: A toast, to the end of the world.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: So you would rather spend your last days in complete solitude?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: If I leave you behind, I'll never find liberation.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I too will follow you along this lonely path.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine and I talk about our lonely fates.
If you had to choose between day or night,
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: which one would get the ax?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Day is on the chopping block.
Night is on the chopping block.
After all, we are creatures of the night.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: We are more accustomed to living in the dark.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Therefore it's a natural choice for us to abandon the light of day.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: You've gone insane!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Are you attempting to stand against the tides of fate?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Such a curse cannot be lifted so easily!
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I speak with Guillotine about the importance of day and night.
My eye feels more uncomfortable than usual.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Do you think it's all right to lift the seal for a moment?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Not here!
You'll be in a world of hurt with Ingrid.
I should have figured as much.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Are you worried I will go berserk?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, don't worry.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: You are my only deterrent.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: There are many forces out there attempting to suppress this body.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine and I speak about the frustration of being sealed away.
The Big O is after me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Can I hide here momentarily?
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Sure.
Thanks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: They must have sensed my energy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: They won't be able to follow me here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I'll explain the details later.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: I would appreciate it if you stopped looking at me like that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Guillotine

adviseScripts.text: Guillotine and I continued to have a discussion as we played Hide and Go Seek.
